communications.subject: RE: Freedom of Information Act Request #COW2018000831
communications.communication:
That is the correct address. We aren't sure why it was returned. Also, I tried to register the case using my FOIA online account, but it's saying that's not possible. Any tips? 

Thanks, 

Matthew Hoppock

communications.subject: RE: Freedom of Information Act Request #COW2018000831
communications.communication:
Good morning Matthew,

Are you inquiring about COW2018000831 or COW2018000844? It looks like the original ack letter for COW2018000844 did not include a PIN. Please select “No” on the screen below. The case should then appear in your portal.

[cid:image001.png@01D97F2F.87392540]
Additionally, please let us know if you are still interested in COW2018000844 by responding to the attached correspondence.

Thank you,
Samantha

communications.subject: RE: Freedom of Information Act Request #COW2018000831
communications.communication:
This is regarding COW2018000844. The letter you just attached is from March, but I have never seen it before today. Yes, we want to proceed and still want the records. The April 4 Ack letter that I received yesterday has a tracking number of COW2018000844 and a PIN of 782745. However, I can't add that to my USCIS account using the tracking number and PIN. 

Please let me know if you need anything else from me on this request to complete processing it. Thank you. 

Matthew Hoppock

                        Re:    Freedom of Information Act Request No. ATFY22-145

Dear Mr. Manning:

This letter acknowledges receipt of your Freedom of Information Act ("FOIA") request dated September 17, 2022, and received in this Office on September 19, 2022, in which you requested a copy of all Civil Investigative Demands sent during the month of August, 2022.   We assigned your request tracking number ATFY22-145.  Please refer to this number in any future correspondence concerning your request.

           To the extent that your request requires a search in another Office, consultations with other Department of Justice components or another agency, and/or involves a voluminous amount of material, your request falls within "unusual circumstances."  See 5 U.S.C. § 552(a)(6)(B)(i)-(iii).  Accordingly, we will need to extend the time limit to respond to your request beyond the ten additional days provided by the statute.

We assign and process requests on a multitrack basis.  The time needed to complete our work on your request will depend on several factors, including the complexity of our records search, the volume and complexity of any material located, and the order of receipt of your request.  At this time, we have assigned your request to the complex track.  In an effort to speed up our process, you may wish to narrow the scope of your request to limit the number of potentially responsive records. You can also agree to an alternative time frame for processing, should records be located.  Any decision with regard to fees will be made after we determine whether fees will apply to this request.

We regret the necessity of this delay, but we assure you that your request will be processed as soon as possible. If you have any questions or wish to discuss reformulation or an alternative time frame for the processing of your request, you may contact this Office by telephone at the above number, or you may write to the above address.  You may contact our FOIA Public Liaison, Wayne Foster, at the above telephone number or address to discuss any aspect of your request.

Additionally, you may contact the Office of Government Information Services ("OGIS") at the National Archives and Records Administration to inquire about the FOIA mediation services they offer. The contact information for OGIS is as follows: Office of Government Information Services, National Archives and Records Administration, Room 2510, 8601 Adelphi Road, College Park, Maryland 20740-6001; e-mail at ogis@nara.gov<mailto:ogis@nara.gov>; telephone at 202-741-5770; toll free at 1-877-684-6448; or facsimile at 202-741-5769.

                                                                                   Sincerely,

FOIA/Privacy Act Unit
Antitrust Division

Hi Eric,
 
Thank you for the list of State Chartered CUs regulated by Connecticut Department of Banking, however there was a request for fields of membership of Connecticut State Chartered CUs. 
We are still interested in the document (or set of documents) containing the most recent fields of membership for these 26 State Chartered CUs. 
Such documents were provided to us by your department in 2015. Considering this, your department should maintain such information and is responsible for providing it per public request. 
Please provide us with the most recent FOM of active state-chartered credit unions to fulfil our request.

communications.subject: RE: Connecticut Freedom of Information Act Request: Connecticut State Chartered CUs Fields of Membership
communications.communication:
Mr. Brownell:

Thank you. The Department of Banking is transitioning to a new online FOI management system called GovQA, accessible on the Department webpage:  https://FOI-Freedom-of-Information-Requests. To maximize efficiency in processing and tracking requests the Department recommends that consumers, both individuals and entities processing requests, utilize the GovQA portal.

I have not neglected your CT FOI Act request, as clarified on September 7th.  The Department is seeking to upload your request into the GovQA platform.  I am in communication with the Division responsible for managing the “financial institutions” records to which you refer, and I expect to issue a final response by September 29th at the latest, hopefully by September 21st.  (I will be away September 22nd – September 25th).  Please note that the Connecticut Freedom of Information Commission interprets ‘promptly’ under CGS Section 1‑19(a), as “ … quickly and without undue delay, [considering] all of the factors presented by a particular request.  Because the facts are going to vary, and vary in significance in each case, the Commission cannot definitively set out in this opinion all of the factors that should be considered in determining promptness…” See Advisory Opinion 51<https://www.state.ct.us/foi/Advisory_Opinions_&_Dec/AO_51.htm>.  If you believe your request is urgent and/ or should be prioritized above others, please provide an explanation for that proposition.


Very truly yours,
[cid:image001.png@01D9EB16.A23ACA30]

communications.subject: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: FOIL Request for Records Related to Communications with American Academy of Pediatrics and Council on School Health (Berne-knox-westerlo Central School District)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

I am seeking all records related to the American Academy of Pediatrics (AAP) and the Council on School Health (COSH), including any communications or correspondence between the school district and these organizations, or any other party that may have provided information to the district from these organizations.

To help identify responsive records, you can limit your time period to 1/1/2017 until the date of final response; also I request that you search for the following terms, which are focused on the American Academy of Pediatrics and its affiliated organizations:

"American Academy of Pediatrics"
"AAP"
"Council on School Health"
"COSH"
"pediatric"
"child health"
"school health"

Please include records of any type, including but not limited to emails, letters, memoranda, reports, meeting minutes, presentations, and any other records of communication or correspondence between the American Academy of Pediatrics, the Council on School Health, and the school district or any other party that may have provided information to the district from these organizations.

If no records are responsive to this request, please provide a certification of that fact pursuant to Public Officers Law §89(3), and inform me of the district's obligations under LGS-01 to retain records until any appeal has been resolved.

If any records are withheld, please provide an explanation of the legal basis for the withholding.

If my request is denied in whole or in part, please provide a written explanation of the reasons for the denial.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jackson Parker

communications.subject: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: Holocaust Survey (Berne-knox-westerlo Central School District)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

By way of background, on August 10, 2022, Governor Kathy Hochul signed into law Chapter 490 of the Laws of 2022 requiring a survey regarding instruction on the Holocaust within New York State public school districts. Through the survey, superintendents are required to attest that the district is teaching about the Holocaust appropriately as part of classroom instruction aligned with the NYS Social Studies Learning Standards and §801 of Education Law.

In October 2022, Deputy Commissioner Angelique Johnson-Dingle sent a memo to public school superintendents including a copy of that survey and instructions for accessing and submitting the survey via the SED Monitoring and Vendor Performance System in the NYSED Business Portal.

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request all of the Holocaust Instruction Survey responses submitted since August 10, 2022.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jackson Parker

communications.subject: RE: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: Holocaust Survey (Berne-knox-westerlo Central School District)

communications.subject: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: EDSCLS (Berne-knox-westerlo Central School District)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

All communications, reports, plans, documentations, calendar entries or agreements between district and BOCES and or third parties regarding school climate surveys (i.e. EDSCLS) for the previous 5 years.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jackson Parker

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: Arghese Alengada Police Report 2019-2020 (Alameda Police Department)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All police reports from the case against Arghese Alengada, also known as Father George  at St. Joseph Basilica, in Alameda and Oakland, Alameda County, California. Please provide the records from January 1st, 2019 through September 18, 2023.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Victoria Anderer

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: FOIA - FBI - Jim Brown
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

All records relating to or mentioning James Nathaniel Brown (February 17, 1936 – May 18, 2023), most commonly known as Jim Brown - an American football player (NFL), civil rights activist, and actor (see: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jim_Brown)

Please conduct a thorough search of the Central Records System, including but not limited to the Electronic Surveillance (ELSUR) Indices, the Physical Surveillance (FISUR) Indices, the Microphone Surveillance (MISUR) Indices, and the Technical Surveillance (TESUR) Indices - for both main-file records and cross-reference records for all relevant names, individuals, agencies and companies. 

If any potentially responsive records have been destroyed and/or transferred to NARA, then I request copies of the destruction or transfer slips as well as any other documentation relating to, mentioning or describing said transfer or destruction, to include but not be limited to confirmation that the Bureau has no other copies of said records. If previously released records are available, then I request a rolling release consisting of those records while additional records are located and processed for release.

Please see the following major news article as proof of death: https://apnews.com/article/nfl-jim-brown-03d88c7da08840a0921ae8d8dd0a6aaa

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

J Ader

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not. 

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires. 

Sincerely, 

Rose Terse 

Upload documents directly: https://accounts.muckrock.com/accounts/login/?next=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.muckrock.com%2Faccounts%2Flogin%2F%3Fnext%3D%252Faccounts%252Fagency_login%252Fking-county-sheriffs-office-2399%252Fsuas-operations-152742%252F%253Femail%253Dkcso%252540mycusthelp.net&url_auth_token=AAATlkMFitx2rEEBFUawwtUL2VE%3A1qnrab%3AGk61PcNSHkkfAwlzpAAyFDEgsxJ5EEqRUCTUiY9gtRA” The KCSO is experiencing a high volume of open requests, over 1,300 of which came in prior to your request. In order to ensure an adequate response, your request requires clarification. We have identified an MS Excel list of 3,267 flight events which includes the following data elements: - Flight Date/Time - Flight Title (i.e. case number, if included) - Flight Description (i.e. case related or training*, etc., if included) - Takeoff Lat/Long (i.e. location) - Air Time - Air Seconds *note: most training events are blank This list includes Lat/Long so requires review of each event where there is a case number (investigation) to determine case status prior to release of the list. Open and active investigations are categorically exempt so we would not provide lat/long information. Based on current request volume and the time to review and determine each case status, we would anticipate completion of our review by April 10, 2023. If we are unable to meet this self-imposed deadline, we will let you know, and if we're able to provide a response sooner, we will certainly do so. If, however, you're willing for us to remove the "Takeoff Lat/Long" column, we can provide a response much sooner. If we don't hear from you by , we will proceed with review of each individual investigation and you can expect a response by November 9, 2023 April 10, 2023. Your request is subject to fees as allowed under King County Ordinance 18949 and the Public Records Act, RCW 42.56.120. Please visit our and select "What is the cost to obtain records" for more information. Once we have determined the scope of your request and responsive records, we may provide an estimate for fees requiring 10% down prior to processing your request. website PLEASE NOTE: Per RCW 42.56.120(4), the KCSO reserves the right to close a records request after 30 days if a requester does not inspect, view, download, and/or pick up the records we provide. There is no obligation for us to continue producing records that are not being collected by a requester. RCW 42.56.120(4) states that if an installment of a records request is not claimed or reviewed, the agency is not obligated to fulfill the balance of the request. WAC 44-14-04006(1) states that a records request has been fulfilled and can be closed if an entirely unclear request has not been clarified,a request or installment has not been claimed or reviewed, or the requester cancels the request. 
Please reply directly to this message or log in to the Online Request System if you have any questions or would like to clarify or cancel this request. Sincerely, Kimberly Petty | Legal & Public Disclosure Program Manager Sheriff's Administration - Policy Direction King County Sheriff's Office www.kingcounty.gov/sheriff

title: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: Personnel and disciplinary records, subject: fmr. Police Officer Yoheliza Yanez

communications.subject: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: Personnel and disciplinary records, subject: fmr. Police Officer Yoheliza Yanez
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

Personnel and the complete disciplinary record of former Police Officer Yoheliza Yanez and all disciplinary records that identify P.O. Yoheliza Yanez as a subject. For specificity and to rule out duplicates, PO Yoheliza Yanez was arrested on October 14, 2022 in the confines of the 102 Precinct in the County of Queens, New York. 

Divisions that may hold responsive records include Internal Affairs, Employment Management, and Department Advocate's Office; however, any record used to evaluate performance toward the subject's continued employment or promotion should be considered responsive.

In accordance with the Freedom of Information Law as amended by Chapter 96 of the Laws of New York of 2020, records that may be released include "the complaints, allegations, and charges against an employee; the name of the employee complained of or charged; the transcript of any disciplinary trial or hearing, including any exhibits introduced at such trial or hearing; the disposition of any disciplinary proceeding; and the final written opinion or memorandum supporting the disposition and discipline imposed including the agency's complete factual findings and its analysis of the conduct and appropriate discipline of the covered employee."

Under precedent, Freedom of Information Law uses a "balancing test" method of weighing privacy interests favoring redaction/denial against the public interest in favor of disclosure. This matter is of clear public interest for the following reasons: P.O. Yoheliza Yanez has been publicly accused of engaging in an off-duty act of domestic violence in the County of Queens: https://qns.com/2022/10/two-off-duty-nypd-officers-cuffed-in-kew-gardens-domestic-incident/

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Kim Smith

Daniella Jimenez
